    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4

    ValueWithAttributes PayloadStdAttributes

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4:PayloadStdAttributes

      • Description

        The standard attributes that appear on the root element for all OpenTravel messages.

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<PayloadStdAttributes altLangID="es" correlationID="Example String Value" echoToken="Example String Value" primaryLangID="en" retransmissionIndicatorInd="true" sequenceNmbr="Example String Value" target="Test" targetName="Example String Value" timeStamp="2011-01-24T09:45:00-06:00" transactionIdentifier="Example String Value" transactionStatusCode="Start" version="12" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4"/>

      Example JSON

      {
  "PayloadStdAttributes" : {
    "value" : null,
    "echoToken" : "Example String Value",
    "timeStamp" : "2011-01-24T09:45:00-06:00",
    "target" : "Test",
    "targetName" : "Example String Value",
    "version" : 12,
    "transactionIdentifier" : "Example String Value",
    "sequenceNmbr" : "Example String Value",
    "transactionStatusCode" : "Start",
    "correlationID" : "Example String Value",
    "primaryLangID" : "en",
    "altLangID" : "es",
    "retransmissionIndicatorInd" : true
  }
}

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        echoToken
        Implementer: A reference for additional message identification, assigned by the requesting host system. When a request message includes an echo token the corresponding response message MUST include an echo token with an identical value.
        Details
        Type StringShort
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        timeStamp
        YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ with time values using the 24 hour clock: 20 November 2003, 1:59:38 pm UTC becomes 2003-11-20T13:59:38Z
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:dateTime
        Example Value 2011-01-24T09:45:00-06:00
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        target
        Test or Production target system indicator.
        Details
        Type TargetEnvironment_Enum
        Example Value Test
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        targetName
        The name of the Test or Production system.
        Details
        Type StringShort
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        version
        The OpenTravel message version indicated by a decimal value.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:decimal
        Example Value 12
        Required true
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        transactionIdentifier
        Unique identifier to relate all messages within a transaction (e.g. this would be sent in all request and response messages that are part of an on-going transaction).
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:string
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        sequenceNmbr
        Implementer: Message resynchronization typically is required if a system has been off-line and needs to retrieve messages that were missed.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:string
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        transactionStatusCode
        This indicates where this message falls within a sequence of messages.
        Details
        Type TransactionStatusCode_Enum
        Example Value Start
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        correlationID
        Allows end-to-end correlation of log messages with the corresponding Web service message throughout the processing of the Web service message.
        Details
        Type StringShort
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        primaryLangID
        ISO 639 (3) character language codes: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lists_of_ISO_639_codes
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:language
        Example Value en
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        altLangID
        ISO 639 (3) character language codes: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lists_of_ISO_639_codes
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:language
        Example Value es
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1

      • Indicator Summary

        Indicators 
        Name Description
        retransmissionIndicatorInd
        Implementer: It is recommended that this attribute is used (i.e., set to TRUE) only when a message is retransmitted.
